    <text id="B0445T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell forwards receipts for clothing issued.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R.F. &amp;
                        A.L.</abbr><lb/><abbr expan="HeadQuarters">Headqrs</abbr> 9th <abbr
                            expan="Sub-District">Sub Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Roswell Waldo<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner"
                        >A.S.A.Comr</abbr><lb/>Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-09-14"><abbr expan="September">Sept.</abbr> 14 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to return herewith Receipt Rolls for clothing issued by you. You
                    will please enter it upon <abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> Jordan's Rolls
                    enclosed to you with my Letter of 11th inst.</p>

                <p>A supply of Clothing Rolls is this day sent you.</p>

                <p>The headings and signature to certificate will be left blank.</p>

                <p>The signatures of the recipients will be witnessed by you.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient Servant">Obedt
                        St</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/>Sub <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst
                        Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
